<HR size="1" color="#12350C">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
I participated in a lot of RvR over the holidays.  One thing I quickly discovered is that it was very difficult for me to ever actually cast any spells.  The main reason I couldn't cast was video lag.  I would attempt to move into range, but my system was bogged down due to the number of players in the vicinity.   I would usually end of mezzed, nuked, or shot by an archer before I could ever get in range and target someone.  Not really anything you can do to counter that.  Some other situations occured though that hopefully do have solutions.  Would appreciate any pointers from those of you who have figured out how to cast in these situations.  <P>Here are some specific situations I found myself in:<P>1)  Seiging a keep.  We were seiging a keep controlled by only a few Hibernians. They had a couple of archers and casters up on top of the ramparts shooting/casting down on us.  I could clearly see an archer on top of one of the walls.  However, every time I attempted to cast, I got a "Target not in view" message.   Is there any way at all to cast a spell at a player on top of a rampart?<P>2)  Defending a milegate from top of rampart.  After discovering the problems of casting spells on players on top of ramparts when I was on a keep seige, I decided to go to the top of the milegate and cast from there.  I was told by another player that in order to cast on someone down on the ground, you had to jump first then cast.  This only worked every once in a while.  I would jump first and immediately hit a spell hotkey.  Most of the times I got "target not in view" message.  I was standing on the sides of the milegate, not in the middle where the archer slits are.  I was always casting on players directly in front of the gate so range was not an issue.  If casters must always jump in order to cast from the top of a milegate, then that is a really bad design decision.  There should be some tactical advantage to casting from that location, i.e. unfetttered casting.  The wall of the milegate rampart should not block line of sight for casters standing on top of it.  One thing I discovered is that enemy archers and casters had no problems attacking me.  I was constantly getting sniped by archers and hit with an AE DOT.   What I don't understand is why was it so easy for the enemy to hit me while I was on top of the milegate rampart when it was impossible for me to cast on them when they were on top of a keep rampart.  Are there different line of sight rules for casting from the ground for keeps and milegates?<P>3)  Defending a milegate from the ground.  When I found it difficult to cast from the top of a milegate, I moved down to the ground.  I tried two different approaches.  One approach was to stand beside the gate and cast on the enemy when they ran through.  They usually didn't survive very long so at most I only got one spell off.  The second approach was to face the gate from a distance so I could see through to the other side.  That way I could target the enemy on the other side.  What I would try to do is activate Quickcast, run up to the gate to get in range, and then cast either AE mez oe AE STR/CON debuff.  Video lag usually prevented me from ever casting.  What usually ended up happening was that I would get killed by AE nukes from an eldritch (whatever spell has the billowing black clouds) or an archer before I could ever get a spell off.  I tried this on numerous occasion, but was only able to cast a spell once or twice.<P>The only times I found myself in situations where I could regularly cast was when both forces were out in open terrain in a standoff situation.  I could position myself so that I could Quickcast, run up to get in range, and cast a spell.  I successfully cast several mezzes and debuffs in this situation.<P>Sorry for the long winded post but I need some help here.  RvR isn't very fun right now, primarily due to the major video lag problems.  But that is something that everyone has to deal with.  But when I can actually do something usefuldespite the video lag, I find myself still ineffective for the most part because of the problems I described.  Any tips on how to reliable cast spells in RvR are greatly appreciated. <P>Thanks<BR>Galtin
</FONT>
