<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
The line of sight problems probably won't get resolved until they introduce the new engine sometime this year.  Jumping at the top of the ramparts does work.  You have to spam the spell key while jumping.  Just be aware anyone outside can target you easily and cast/shoot regardless of whether or not they have LOS when you're jumping.  Range from the ramparts is pathetic.  We're far more useful debuffing/mez'ing the attackers at the doors.<P>Lag around alot of people is a problem for almost everyone.  Even people with fast systems and lots of RAM report bad memory leaks, and continually have to relog.  I run on a Athlon 1100, 384 megs ram, Geforce 2 64 meg DDR, and my video slows to a crawl frequently in large battles.  If I thought upgrading my PC would fix the problem, then I would.<P>We're playing on a recycled game engine that was patched to make Camelot work.  They've done a fairly good job, but I get the feeling they're waiting for the new engine to fix alot of these bugs.  Hopefully they make it possible to defend a keep without casting through doors.
</FONT>
