<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Like probably everyone I too have had difficulty casting spells in RvR due to lag/choppy video. A new display adapter card didn't solve the problem by any means but did help quite a bit. <P>One strategy I've found useful when the video gets real choppy is to pan the camera angle way down. Panning down effectively cuts the clipping plane and can allow you to move around and get spells off a little easier. <P>Sometimes logging off and back on the game seems to help tremndously with video lag (memory leak somewhere).
</FONT>
